.TH "xdr_inline_pages" 9 "xdr_inline_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xdr_inline_pages \- Prepare receive buffer for a large reply
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xdr_inline_pages
.BI "(struct xdr_buf *xdr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "struct page **pages "  ","
.BI "unsigned int base "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xdr" 12
xdr_buf into which reply will be placed
.IP "offset" 12
expected offset where data payload will start, in bytes
.IP "pages" 12
vector of struct page pointers
.IP "base" 12
offset in first page where receive should start, in bytes
.IP "len" 12
expected size of the upper layer data payload, in bytes
